(309, 'Demon Armor', 'HA', 'While wearing this armor, you gain a +1 bonus to AC, and you can understand and speak Abyssal. In addition, the armor\'s clawed gauntlets turn unarmed strikes with your hands into magic weapons that deal slashing damage, with a +1 bonus to attack rolls and damage rolls and a damage die of 1d8. \n\n \n\nCurse: Once you don this cursed armor, you can\'t doff it unless you are targeted by the remove curse spell or similar magic. While wearing the armor, you have disadvantage on attack rolls against demons and on saving throws against their spells and special abilities. \n\n \n\nSource: Dungeon Master\'s Guide p. 165', '1', 'very rare, cursed (requires attunement)', '65', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '18', '15', '1'),
(310, 'Dwarven Plate', 'HA', 'While wearing this armor, you gain a +2 bonus to AC. In addition, if an effect moves you against your will along the ground, you can use your reaction to reduce the distance you are moved by up to 10 feet. \n\n \n\nSource: Dungeon Master\'s Guide p. 167', '1', 'very rare', '65', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '18', '15', '1'),
(311, 'Efreeti Chain', 'HA', 'While wearing this armor, you gain a +3 bonus to AC, you are immune to fire damage, and you can understand and speak Primordial. In addition, you can stand on and walk across molten rock as if it were solid ground. \n\n \n\nSource: Dungeon Master\'s Guide p. 167', '1', 'legendary (requires attunement)', '55', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '16', '13', '1'),
(312, 'Mariner\'s Chain Mail', 'HA', 'While wearing this armor, you have a swimming speed equal to your walking speed. In addition, whenever you start your turn underwater with 0 hit points, the armor causes you to rise 60 feet toward the surface. The armor is decorated with fish and shell motifs. \n\n \n\nSource: Dungeon Master\'s Guide p. 181', '1', 'uncommon', '55', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '16', '13', '1'),
