(315, 'Giant Octopus', 'L', 'beast', 'unaligned', '11', '52 (8d10+8)', '10 ft., swim 60 ft.', 17, 13, 13, 4, 10, 4, '', 'Perception +4, Stealth +5', '', '', '', '', 'darkvision 60 ft.', '14', '', '1', 'Source \nMonster Manual, p. 326', 'Hold Breath \nWhile out of water, the octopus can hold its breath for 1 hour.', 'Underwater Camouflage \nThe octopus has advantage on Dexterity (Stealth) checks made while underwater.', 'Water Breathing \nThe octopus can breathe only underwater.', '', '', '', '', 'Tentacles \nMelee Weapon Attack: +5 to hit, reach 15 ft., one target. Hit: 10 (2d6+3) bludgeoning damage. If the target is a creature, it is grappled (escape DC 16). Until this grapple ends, the target is restrained, and the octopus can\'t use its tentacles on another target. \n\n \n\nGrappled: \n\nâ€¢ A grappled creature\'s speed becomes 0, and it can\'t benefit from any bonus to its speed. \n\n \n\nâ€¢ The condition ends if the grappler is incapacitated. \n\n \n\nâ€¢ The condition also ends if an effect removes the grappled creature from the reach of the grappler or grappling effect, such as when a creature is hurled away by the thunderwave spell. \n\n \n\nRestrained: \n\nâ€¢ A restrained creature\'s speed becomes 0, and it can\'t benefit from any bonus to its speed. \n\n \n\nâ€¢ Attack rolls against the creature have advantage, and the creature\'s attack rolls have disadvantage. \n\n \n\nâ€¢ The creature has disadvantage on Dexterity saving throws.', 'Ink Cloud (Recharges after a Short or Long Rest) \nA 20-foot-radius cloud of ink extends all around the octopus if it is underwater. The area is heavily obscured for 1 minute, although a significant current can disperse the ink. After releasing the ink, the octopus can use the Dash action as a bonus action.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
