(330, 'Giant Wasp', 'M', 'beast', 'unaligned', '12', '13 (3d8)', '10 ft., fly 50 ft., swim 50 ft.', 10, 14, 10, 1, 10, 3, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '10', '', '1', 'Source \nMonster Manual, p. 329', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Sting \nSting. Melee Weapon Attack: +4 to hit, reach 5 ft., one creature. Hit: 5 (1d6+2) piercing damage, and the target must make a DC 11 Constitution saving throw, taking 10 (3d6) poison damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. If the poison damage reduces the target to 0 hit points, the target is stable but poisoned for 1 hour, even after regaining hit points, and is paralyzed while poisoned in this way. \n\n \n\nParalyzed: \n\nâ€¢ A paralyzed creature is incapacitated, meaning it can\'t take actions or reactions, and can\'t move or speak. \n\n \n\nâ€¢ The creature automatically fails Strength and Dexterity saving throws. \n\n \n\nâ€¢ Attack rolls against the creature have advantage. \n\n \n\nâ€¢ Any attack that hits the creature is a critical hit if the attacker is within 5 feet of the creature. \n\n \n\nPoisoned: \n\nâ€¢ A poisoned creature has disadvantage on attack rolls and ability checks.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
